column1: #Text=US Libertarian Party presidential candidate Adam Kokesh

#Text=, an Iraq War veteran , activist , radio show host , and currently a candidate for the US Libertarian Party ' s 2020 presidential nomination , spoke with Wikinews to discuss his background , political positions , and campaign for President of the United States .
#Text=Adam Kokesh Image : The Adam Kokesh American Referendum Project .
#Text=Kokesh , who hails from Arizona , has been active in the anti-war movement since returning home from combat in Iraq .

#Text=After an initial honorary discharge from active duty with the US Marine Corp in 2006 , Kokesh was given a general discharge from the Marine Forces Reserve in 2007 after images of him wearing his uniform while participating in a protest with the Iraq Veterans Against the War were published in The Washington Post .
#Text=Kokesh has also been involved in demonstrations in support of free speech , gun rights , and marijuana decriminalization .
#Text=Some of these activities have resulted in his arrest .
#Text=Kokesh previously hosted a show on RT and currently hosts a show on internet radio .
#Text=Politically , Kokesh supported the 2008 and 2012 presidential campaigns of Ron Paul .
#Text=He was a featured speaker at Paul 's Rally for the Republic in 2008 .
#Text=Kokesh ran for US Congress as a Republican in 2010 in New Mexico and for US Senate in Arizona in 2018 .
#Text=He announced his 2020 candidacy in 2013 during a jailhouse interview .

#Text=He has based his campaign on the pledge to begin " dissolving the federal government in a peaceful , orderly manner " and to resign as president and take the title of " Custodian of the Federal Government .
